          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Always play 4-5 tiles minimum:</span> Your opening is a free DWS. Don't waste it on a 3-letter word. Use 5 tiles to maximize the double and refresh your rack for turn 2.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Target the DLS on column/row 4 or 8:</span> Place your highest-value letter on the DLS adjacent to center. This letter gets doubled by DLS AND doubled again by the center DWS = 4× that tile's value.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Prioritize leave over 4 extra points:</span> If choosing between a 30-point opener (leave: Q-V) and a 26-point opener (leave: E-R), take the 26. Your turn 2-3 will more than recover the difference.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Don't extend to row/column 1 or 15:</span> Opening words that reach the edge give your opponent access to TWS on turn 2. Keep your opener contained to rows 4-12 to avoid gifting premium squares.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
